{
  "texts": [
    "Retrieval AnalysisSince the retrieved passages may not cover all gold answers (Gao et al., 2023b), we calibrate the model's correctness metrics, so that we can directly inspect the model's ability to capture answers in the given passages.",
    "Specifically, we ignore gold answers that are not recalled by the top 5 retrieved passages when computing correctness metrics.",
    "We observe that our fine-grained methods (f.g. RL; f.g. RS; f.g.(RS+RL)) can capture around 70% of whatever is already captured by the passages on ASQA and QAMPARI, and this number becomes more than 90% on ELI5.",
    "In other words, our trained LLMs are effective in locating answers within retrieved passages, although there is still space to improve the models' correctness recall by capturing the remaining answers in the passages.",
    "On the Table 2: Ablation study results."
  ]
}